Flex is specified in the CSS, no JS needed

First create your element in the HTML and give it a class

    &lt;div class=&quot;my__flexbox&quot;&gt;This will be a flexbox&lt;/div&gt;

Then using CSS you would reference your class and add a `display: flex` rule.

    .my__flexbox {
        display: flex;
    }

You have to create a container such as *div* in html and assign it a class.
HTML would look like this:

    &lt;div classname=&quot;flexbox-container&quot;&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
and the CSS goes like this:

    .flexbox-container {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column; //Default direction is row. Everything inside this 
                            container would be in a single row.
    }

To learn more about flexbox, you can visit: https://learn.freecodecamp.org/responsive-web-design/css-flexbox

