Right now, the *issue* with your code is that you have currently *2 rows* and you are using positions and margins to force them to stick together.

When you do a *mobile responsive* change, you&#39;ll need to fix alot of these which may make it complicated.

Instead, focus on making the *parent div relatively positioned* and the *child divs to be absolutely positioned to its parent*. 

That way, when you can use *media query* and easily adjust the values for each breakpoint when it comes to responsiveness.

**Try this:**

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    .project-name {
      border-bottom: 100px solid #ffffff;
      border-right: 50px solid transparent;
      height: 0;
      width: 80%;
      background-color: transparent;
      position: absolute;
      bottom: 100px;
    }

    .project-name h2 {
      margin-top: 40px;
    }

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;link href=&quot;https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.0.0/css/bootstrap.min.css&quot; rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot;/&gt;

    &lt;div class=&quot;container&quot;&gt;
